HEADWORD: Trophic
<hw>Troph"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ nursing. See
<er>Trophi</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>Of or connected with
nutrition; nitritional; nourishing; <as>as, the so-called
<ex>trophic</ex> nerves, which have a direct influence on
nutrition</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

